<L>__{interior license shop day}
<A>__{the machines are idle; no one is in the room but malcolm. he starts to reach inside his jacket when barnes sticks his head in.}
<C>__{guard barnes}
<D>__{you taking the yard or not?}
<C>__{malcolm}
<D>__{i'm staying.}
<C>__{guard barnes}
<D>__{then give me a butt.}
<A>__{malcolm takes out a half filled pack of cigarettes, about to offer one, then pauses. malcolm hands him the pack of cigarettes.}
<C>__{malcolm}
<D>__{take 'em. i don't smoke no more.}
<A>__{he takes the pack happily and goes. malcolm reaches into his jacket again, takes out a book. we see its title: mahatma gandhi's _my struggle_. he sits next to the license press to read.}
